cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.NE 

The paper presents a novel computational approach for inferring biological function for a set of genes with previously unknown function, given a set of genes with well-known information. The approach is based on clustering techniques and guilt-by-association principle. Therefore, it involves machine learning and data mining techniques (cs.LG), as well as database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for knowledge representation and inference. The proposed method also involves the analysis of gene expression data, which falls under computational biology and bioinformatics (cs.CE). Finally, the approach is applied to biological networks, which can be modeled using neural networks (cs.NE).
